./rootfs.ext2: rootfs built from buildroot project
./bzImage_fst_success: my first successful-boot image
./config_fst_success.txt: .config backup for bzImage_fst_success
./bzImage_sec_success: my second successfull-boot image, make compile time far more shorter
./config_sec_success.txt: .config backup for bzImage_sec_success
./config_thd_success.txt: .config backup for third build, shorten to about 44 min

1. The process of make initrd for our host kernel.

  472  /usr/lib/dracut/skipcpio initrd.img-6.12.63+deb13-amd64 > initramfs-main.cpio
  473  ls
  474  file initramfs-main.cpio 
  475  cddd
  476  cd
  477  cd workspace/buildroot/
  478  qemu-system-x86_64 -kernel /tmp/vmlinuz-6.12.63+deb13-amd64 -drive file=output/images/rootfs.ext2,format=raw,if=ide -nographic -append "root=/dev/sda rootfstype=ext2 console=ttyS0" -initrd /tmp/test/initramfs-main.cpio 
  479  cd /tmp/test
  480  ls
  481  file initramfs-main.cpio 
  482  ls
  483  zstd -d -c initramfs-main.cpio > /tmp/initramfs-main.cpio.uncompressed
  484  mv ../initramfs-main.cpio.uncompressed .
  485  ls
  486  file initramfs-main.cpio.uncompressed 
  487  mkdir initramfs-root
  488  cd initramfs-root/
  489  cpio -id < ../initramfs-main.cpio.uncompressed 
  490  ls
  491  rm -rf *
  492  ls
  493  sudo cpio -id < ../initramfs-main.cpio.uncompressed 
  494  ls
  495  find .|cpio -o -H newc|gzip -9 > /tmp/initrd-final.gz
  496  rm -rf /tmp/initrd-final.gz 
  497  sudo find .|cpio -o -H newc|gzip -9 > /tmp/initrd-final.gz
  498  rm -rf /tmp/initrd-final.gz 
  499  find .|sudo cpio -o -H newc|gzip -9 > /tmp/initrd-final.gz
  500  cd
  501  cd workspace/buildroot/

2.Boot host kernel with buildroot-built rootfs command

qemu-system-x86_64 -kernel /tmp/vmlinuz-6.12.63+deb13-amd64 -initrd /tmp/initrd-final.gz -hda output/images/rootfs.ext2 -nographic -append "root=/dev/sda rootfstype=ext2 console=ttyS0 rootwait" -m 1024

or

qemu-system-x86_64 -kernel /tmp/vmlinuz-6.12.63+deb13-amd64 -initrd /tmp/initrd-final.gz -drive file=output/images/rootfs.ext2,format=raw,if=virtio -nographic -append "root=/dev/vda rootfstype=ext2 console=ttyS0 rootwait" -m 1024

3.host version
zxy@debian:~/workspace/kernel/linux_kernel/host_kernel_and_initrd$ uname -a
Linux debian 6.12.73+deb13-amd64 #1 SMP PREEMPT_DYNAMIC Debian 6.12.73-1 (2026-02-17) x86_64 GNU/Linux

4.first successfully build kernel(use about 500 min)
boot command:
qemu-system-x86_64 \
  -kernel ~/workspace/30Gsda5/linux-6.12.75/arch/x86/boot/bzImage \
  -hda ~/workspace/buildroot/output/images/rootfs.ext2 \
  -append "root=/dev/sda rootfstype=ext2 console=ttyS0,115200 rootwait systemd.log_level=debug systemd.log_target=console" \
  -nographic -m 1024

5.second successfully build kernel(use about 77 min)
boot command is the same as 4, but sometimes will encounter kernel panic error:
[ 0.461059] Kernel panic - not syncing: IO-APIC + timer doesn't work! Boot with apic=debug and send a report. Then try bootin.

Use below command to boot:
qemu-system-x86_64 \
  -kernel ./bzImage_sec_success \
  -hda ~/workspace/buildroot/output/images/rootfs.ext2 \
  -append "root=/dev/sda rootfstype=ext2 console=ttyS0,115200 noapic rootwait s\
  -nographic -m 1024

Please pay attention to the noapic in the -append parameter.

6.third successfully build kernel(use about 44 min)
install kernel steps(after build the kernel)
 1994  cd 30Gsda5/
 1995  ls
 1996  cd linux-6.12.75/
 1997  ls
 1998  make -j2 bindeb-pkg
 1999  cd ..
 2000  ls
 2001  sudo dpkg -i linux-image-6.12.75-zxy-extra_6.12.75-zxy-extra-2_amd64.deb linux-headers-6.12.75-zxy-extra_6.12.75-zxy-extra-2_amd64.deb 
 2002  sudo update-grub

install kernel module(take helloworld.ko for example, we choose <M> for this module)
 1996  cd /lib/modules/6.12.75-zxy-extra/
 1997  ls
 1998  find -name *hello*
 1999  uname -r
 2000  sudo modprobe ./kernel/drivers/helloworld/helloworld.ko 
 2001  dmesg|tail -n 19

To remove the module: sudo rmmod helloworld

7. Remove kernel steps(after install kernel)
 1991  dpkg --list | grep linux-image
 1992  dpkg --list | grep linux-headers
 1993  uname -a
 1994  sudo apt purge linux-image-6.12.63+deb13-amd64                linux-headers-6.12.63+deb13-amd64                linux-headers-6.12.63+deb13-common                linux-image-6.12.75-zxy-extra                linux-headers-6.12.75-zxy-extra
 1995  ls /lib/modules/6.12.75-zxy-extra
 1996  ls /lib/modules/
 1997  ls /etc/kernel/prerm.d/
 1998  dpkg -l | grep 6.12.75-zxy-extra
 1999  sudo apt autoremove --purge
 2000  sudo update-grub
 2001  dpkg --list | grep -E "6.12.63|6.12.75"

